# {{context|colloquial|lang=en}} To make a show of [[bravery]] despite one's fears; to put on a brave front.
#* '''2011''', {{w|Norman Davies}}, ''Vanished Kingdoms'', Penguin 2012, p. 6:
#*: Those who seriously believe ‘There'll always be an England’ are '''whistling in the dark'''.
# {{context|idiomatic|US|lang=en}} To speak of something despite having little [[knowledge]] of it.

